COMMIT BEST PRACTICE:

1.our commit nit be so small (like every single changes)
  not to be so large (like entire a feature)
  it should represent a "LOGICAL STEP"
  because whole purpose is we can come back to last step.
  we normally use 5 to 10 commit per day!

2.use meaningful and present term on message!
  if we have problem in naming, it's probably we need to break our commit!
  present term means : using fix the bug
                       instead using fixed the bug!
